OL,3,CThe tiny robot which could
OL,4,Crevolutionise cancer diagnosis
OL,6,FThe robots, measuring 21mm in diameter
OL,7,F- about the size of a 1p piece - use a
OL,8,F3D shape known as an oloid to give
OL,9,Fthem a previously impossible range of
OL,10,Fmotion, so that they can roll inside
OL,11,Fthe body.
OL,13,FThe resulting scans are sophisticated
OL,14,Fenough to allow clinicians to make
OL,15,Fcross-sectional images mimicing those
OL,16,Fgenerated by a standard biopsy, in
OL,17,Fwhich a sample of tissue is sliced
OL,18,Finto thin layers and placed on a slide
OL,19,Fto be examined under a microscope.
